{'book': {'publisher': 'Harrison House Publishers', 'synopsis': "When a child is born, doctors and family encourage the new parents to provide three elements essential to the survival of the new born: love, nourishment, and protection. These same elements are vital for every new Christian as well. This workbook will help those new to the Christian faith find these basics for survival.<br/>Getting a Grip on the Basics is a powerful study tool designed to help Christians find and experience the love of God, receive spiritual nourishment, and rest in the protective care of the Lord and His Word. Getting a Grip on the Basics will help ground new Christians in the fundamentals found in the Word of God and renew mature Christians in the basics of their faith.<br/>Here's What You'll Discover... • How to Become a Christian • How to Be Sure You are a Christian • How to Develop Your Relationship with God • How to Develop Your Prayer Life • How to Hear from God • How to Obey God • How to Experience God's Love and Forgiveness • How to be Filled With the Holy Spirit • How to be Sure You are Filled With the Holy Spirit • How to Grow and Develop Your Faith • How to Experience the Abundant Life • How to be an Overcomer • How to Serve God", 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/82/61/9781577948261.jpg', 'title_long': 'Getting a Grip on the Basics: Discover the Fundamentals of Christian Faith in 13 Sessions (The Basics With Beth Bible Study Series)', 'dimensions': 'Height: 11 Inches, Length: 8.5 Inches, Weight: 0.70106999316 Pounds, Width: 0.33 Inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 8.5}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 0.33}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 0.70106999316}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 11}}, 'pages': 144, 'date_published': '2006-04-30', 'subjects': ['Christian Books & Bibles', 'Christian Living', 'Faith', 'Education', 'Ministry & Evangelism', 'Discipleship', 'Religion & Spirituality', 'Worsh